
Pompiedom - simple small status update program


TO INSTALL

1. Download a copy from github.com/pstuifzand/pompiedom
2. Create a symbolic link to inc and htdocs/status
3. Copy config.sample.inc.php to config.inc.php
4. Create a database in MySQL
5. Fill in the config values in config.inc.php

    The user of the database only needs SELECT and INSERT privileges.

        - DB_HOST    database host
        - DB_USER    database user
        - DB_PASS    database pass
        - DB_DATABASE database name
        - USERNAME   the username that is shown below every status message
6. Use HTTP authentication to protect the admin directory.

URLs:

http://domain/status/            - list of last 15 messages
http://domain/status/admin/      - admin interface with textarea
http://domain/status/status.php  - Ajax enabled last message  
                                    see pompiedom/htdocs/index.html for a sample

